                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>A Treaty of Economic, Social, and Cultural Collaboration and Collective
                    Self-Defence (Brussels Treaty), March 17, 1948, between Great Britain and
                    Northern Ireland, Belgium, France, Luxembourg, and the Netherlands, was signed
                    at Brussels and entered into force August 25, 1948. For text, see <hi
                        rend="italic">American Foreign Policy, 1950–1955, Basic Documents</hi>,
                    volume I, pages 968–971.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
